values:
Because I am cranky and my head hurts like shit, this post shall be full of ranting. Scroll now if you don't wanna see the crap.

I don't think I need to emphasize how dead I am. With Eoys just one week away, I think my grades will just be flushed down the drain. I did TRY to mug, but my brain is too exhausted to function properly. (I skipped sleep yest again.) meh. So, the point. I am sleepy, cranky, ditzy and about to die for my finals. What a nice prospect.

I told you this post would be full of rants.

Let's see, the only thing good right now, is MI's plotting. But even that doesn't come without guilt. I'm supposed to be effing mugging, for goodness sake!

*sigh*

I came to the realisation this week that I'm not as cracked up as I'm expected to be. And I find that people I care about have been distancing themselves from me. Okay, maybe not people, just two? *shrugs* And all I do is stand there and WATCH thm distance themselves from me. Because I'm just too freaking tired to do anything at all.

Guh.

I really need to mug.

I shouldn't be updating now.

But I am.

*headdesk*

And my aspirin has run out again.

I watched Mr and Mrs Smith today. It was hilarious, to say the least. However, I have some serious doubts regarding the rating level of the movie. Especially for some scenes. Oh, I love John for making the "marriage consultant" ask him the sex question again. The look of glee on his face. :P Mind you, John the character, not Brad Pitt. I'm looking forward to when Batman Begins screens in cinemas. 16 June!!! I came across several YnM sites with dls of doujinshi and bits of the manga. Of course, there's also this huge stash of fanfiction. I'm kind of starting to support Tsuzuki/Hisoka, if only because it's the only canon ship I don't abhor in the show. (Tatsumi/Watari is kinda cute, but it's not exactly canon.) The doujinshi ripped me off. I didn't even have to understand a single word. -_-" The german program has been pretty fun so far. I find myself actually enjoying it. Which is rather surprising, considering the fact that the guys are being a general nuisance as well as overwhelming noise pollution. The only thing I cringe at is the incredibly corny love affair they show us on tape. It's so shallow it's almost crude, to an extent. On a side note, Rui Yi's fun to tease. :P It seems as though I'll never get to watch my tbOVA now, since once the dl hit the 50% mark, the entire thing doesn't even dl anymore. Not the slightest bit. -_-" It's almost as if NO one is seeding. But that's prolly fact. They're all leechers, them. :'( And Tsubasa is taking longer than expected. Meh. And I can't get on the IRC highway to dl Bleach manga. I'm soooo out of luck. It's wrong, isn't it? To whine and pine and be a general pile of goo about something? Only you can't help it. I really don't want to leave. I want to stay and curl up at home in my bed and never peek out from under the covers again. But that doesn't solve it either, because I'm on a one way track; a one-sided conversation. Then even those words that keep surfacing in my mind seem so used. So worthless. I can't remember a time that I haven't felt like this. Because this whole thing is my life.
I've never missed anything this badly in my entire life. Ten years is a long time, but things are always unpredictable. Especially death. I don't know.

I've just re-read the last two chapters of Maya's UL. It's a stroke of genius, really, because if it weren't, it wouldn't have had me glued onto it for the past few hours instead of doing my BioPT for which I am going to be in dire trouble. Nobody does Draco's repartee as well as she does. And that's just it, if Draco doesn't have repartee, that bastard won't be Draco Malfoy. Which understandably, is we all love him so much. Draco = evil sexy bastard = love :D

There are just so many parts of UL which is utterly heart-wrenching, but if you weren't reading carefully, or if you haven't experienced that sort of feeling, that sort of insecurity before, you wouldn't be able to see the beauty of it. If that sort of emotion could be ripped out from hearts and cast into words, it would be exactly as she'd written it. I cannot think of any other way to describe her writing. The emotion's raw and intense and real.

<small>I am so much better off if I didn't keep relating to everything and thinking of someone.</small>

Hm. This may be my imagination, but i think I've just witness some minor tremors just now. I was convinced that my brain was wonky with the utter lack of sleep till I saw the room door swaying back and forth. Of course, this may be a sign of ultimate brain power finally manifesting itself in me such that excess brainwaves shoot out and target nearest doors. But, I shall not think so.

My bro's blasting the house with loud noise from the matrix, so that might be another reason too. Honestly, the crap I put up with just because I have some mislabeled genius as a brother. And for some reason, he's gotten addicted to Fukai Mori. Not my intention, but it prolly had something to do with me, since I had fukai mori playing on repeat track. Still, it was morally unacceptable for him to decide that it would behis new addiction, because that would bring me down to his level and that is just... like I said, morally unacceptable. 

Of course, there's waking up at 6.30am in the morning tomorrow to look forward to. I would think the purpose of having a Sports day would be to let the students at least sleep enough for once. But no, I have to find my conscience at this impeccable hour and decided to help Gen. I'm truly pathetic. Now I don't get more time with my lovely bed.

Ok. Screw this, I'm going mad. As in, more so than normal. I blame this entirely on Jigglypuff. And of course, Matix Reloaded's excessive noise. It's making my head spin.

Take the Spirit Quiz and visit Castle Diqueria.
Whee... So fun... -_-" Well, at least it's over.

First things first,

Happy Birthday Lydia!

Hehex. May you have a wonderful and enriching new year ahead of you! We all went to Lydia's house today and it was really great fun. Basically, we fooled around (ah the luxuries of not haing adults in the house!) and played on her guitar and piano. :P She booked the tennis and badminton court too, so we went to play. Jean was being silly as usual. -_-" I was so-so at badminton, but my tennis sucked bigtime. I finally gave up making a fool of myself so I went upstairs to learn how to play piano chords from Lydia. :P I think around six half, all of us were back at her house and her mother even bought us sushi and pizza. ^_^ but I had to leave early, so I didn't get a taste of the pizza. :( Bleargh. I was glad Lydia liked her gift though, I sewed her name on a pencil case for her, some of personalising it. She said it's nice. ^_^
Secondly, I agreed to make a sort one-shot fic for Liu Hui as a belated birhday and Azure agreed to beta for me. I've got the plot bunny murking around in my head. ^_^ I hope she'll like it.
Thirdly, I've started some class drabbling RPG style, i think I'll go through it and edit it a bit before I post some of it up here. :) I keep the Lord always before me; even at night when my heart exhorts me. Psalms 16:8

Life really really sucks at times. I mean, I'm in school now and my class is making a huge racket, but it's technically not the start of school yet, so no one can reprimand us. Which is good, because if punishments could be meted out, I don';t think will just get a mere scolding. 

Friends. So-called friends I should say. Some times they suck too. They can't even tell when you're really really upset, what's the use of having friends then? I mean, friends are supposed to be there for you when you're sad. Right? Or maybe I'm having dilusions about the term friends. The friends I have make you sad and make you disappointed, that take the heart you present to them and stick a knife in it, if that's not enough, they twist the knife as hard as they can. What's the worst thing though, is that they are already so near to your heart, they have a very good point to aim at you know? The closer your friends are to your heart, the more accurate their aim will be. Wake up and face the hypocrital facts of life. 

That's the reason why we should never let anyone get that close. It's too risky and it's not worth it. What do you get? I mean, you get an occasional gift or two on your birthday, but you get your precious glass heart splattered on the floor like it never mattered. Who knows? Maybe it never really did matter since the whole friendship started. Wouldn't that be nice? To give so much for a friendship and only have it ruined later on. It will happen, it will be ruined, no matter how small the act is, it will still hurt a great deal. 













Life's like that, deal with it or you might as well die.
